00:31:06,280 --> 00:31:08,010
Wan Xinxin didn't kick you out?

559
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:11,200
I realized she's not as unreasonable as I thought.

560
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:13,720
That's the first time I've heard you talk about her like that.

561
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:15,580
Your relationship is improving.

562
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:17,920
Today I was lucky she acted as my shield.

563
00:31:18,520 --> 00:31:22,600
Should I thank her for you?

564
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:28,210
Don't overthink it.

565
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:30,320
It's all because of my mother.

566
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:32,360
I know.

567
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:35,660
Your mother treats her like a daughter-in-law.

568
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:38,860
Wan Xinxin is still more capable than me.

569
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:40,320
Weiwei.

570
00:31:40,640 --> 00:31:43,100
I think you should put yourself in her shoes.

571
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:45,680
No matter what, Wan Xinxin

572
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:47,000
gave birth to my son.

573
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:50,040
And she raised the child all by herself.

574
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:51,680
You're a woman too.

575
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:54,360
If you were in her situation,

576
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:56,690
wouldn't you be emotional as well?

577
00:31:58,160 --> 00:31:59,560
Your perspective has matured.

578
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:02,080
No, these aren't my words.

579
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:03,880
A friend told me this.

580
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:08,440
He said if a couple can't remain married,

581
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:10,370
they don't need to become enemies.

582
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:12,080
If both people are more open-minded

583
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:13,560
and resolve things properly,

584
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:15,560
everyone will be more comfortable.

585
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:17,560
I think that's good advice.

586
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:20,250
Xinxin has changed now.

587
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:22,880
By the way, I heard that she

588
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:24,760
is currently working on some

589
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:27,640
promotional campaign for YouBei toy brand.

590
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:28,970
She's doing quite well,

591
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:32,400
planning to invite Tong Tong and Ma Youyou as guests.

592
00:32:35,480 --> 00:32:38,340
After enough time, it doesn't matter who you marry.

593
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:40,080
A red rose

594
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:42,640
will eventually look like a mosquito smear on the wall.

595
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:46,100
And a white rose becomes just like rice grains on your clothes.

596
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:47,840
That makes a lot of sense.

597
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:52,000
Weiwei.

598
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:56,040
I don't think you need to think that way.

599
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:57,840
I just want to share

600
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:58,970
what I know with you.

601
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:01,330
I don't want to hide anything from you,

602
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:02,690
much less lie to you.

603
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:03,720
That's good.

604
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:06,180
If you have any thoughts about me,

605
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:08,370
tell me early and don't keep it from me.

606
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,820
I don't want to be like Wan Xinxin,

607
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:12,600
being played for a fool.

608
00:33:13,400 --> 00:33:16,000
Look at you, being so petty.

609
00:33:16,680 --> 00:33:17,960
If I had known you'd be like this...

610
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:19,490
I won't talk to you anymore.

611
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:22,000
You're saying I'm petty.

612
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,600
You can't have forgotten what I've done for you.

613
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:25,880
Have you?

614
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:28,320
But now?

615
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:30,760
You spend more time with your son than with me.

616
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:31,960
Tell me, besides you,

617
00:33:32,440 --> 00:33:34,720
your mother, your friends, your relatives,

618
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:36,280
who knows I even exist?

619
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:54,680
Enough.

620
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:57,600
I don't want to talk about this anymore.

621
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:01,180
I don't want to fight with you.

622
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:04,760
I just want to be with you.

623
00:34:05,560 --> 00:34:06,600
Just you and me.

624
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:11,699
I just remembered.

625
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:14,000
I have two car show plans to work on.

626
00:34:14,199 --> 00:34:16,000
You're tired, go to sleep first.

627
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:29,520
What's important this time isn't the product itself,

628
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:32,679
nor what we want our target audience to accept.

629
00:34:32,679 --> 00:34:34,679
I think we need to learn to put ourselves

630
00:34:34,679 --> 00:34:35,880
in our audience's shoes,

631
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:36,920
to understand

632
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:39,280
what they want to get from our products.

633
00:34:39,639 --> 00:34:41,760
My product concept this time

634
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,719
is to bring adults back to a fairy tale world.

635
00:34:44,719 --> 00:34:46,560
Let them become a child,

636
00:34:46,560 --> 00:34:47,679
this way our product

637
00:34:47,679 --> 00:34:49,600
is not just a commodity,

638
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:51,960
it becomes a bridge

639
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:54,639
for communication between adults and children.

640
00:34:54,639 --> 00:34:57,000
So this time I want to create

641
00:34:57,520 --> 00:34:58,580
a fairy tale world.

642
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,560
Using a fairy tale castle

643
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:02,520
to express our theme.

644
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:05,400
We can also incorporate their overall concept

645
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:08,320
and list all the details within it.

646
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:12,960
This solves the problem of having too many product types

647
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:14,840
and unclear targeting.

648
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:17,760
It showcases the strength of our brand.

649
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:21,440
But this is quite a big undertaking.

650
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:23,570
Just finding a venue is difficult.

651
00:35:23,640 --> 00:35:26,480
Our main venue should be at an amusement park.

652
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:28,280
Because an amusement park is

653
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:30,000
a place for family fun.

654
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:31,560
On weekends,

655
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,480
children always beg to go to amusement parks.

656
00:35:33,480 --> 00:35:35,740
Adults have no choice but to go with them.

657
00:35:35,960 --> 00:35:38,240
So amusement parks have

658
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:41,200
the highest public exposure rate for children's products.

659
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:42,960
If our event is successful,

660
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:44,880
I believe it will also be

661
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:47,140
great publicity for the amusement park.

662
00:35:47,640 --> 00:35:48,520
We don't rule out

663
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:50,760
the possibility of long-term cooperation in the future.

664
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:52,680
I understand you want to use their platform to our advantage,

665
00:35:52,680 --> 00:35:54,360
but we need clear branding,

666
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:57,090
otherwise our target audience will be confused.

667
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,960
I've already thought it through, Director Shi.

668
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:01,760
I plan to invite the popular film star

669
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:04,520
Miss Tong Tong to endorse our products.

670
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:08,040
Miss Tong Tong currently has several hit shows

671
00:36:08,040 --> 00:36:09,480
that are extremely popular.

672
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:12,680
All children love her now,

673
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:14,840
and parents really approve of her too.

674
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:16,640
So if we can get Miss Tong Tong,

675
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:19,000
I believe this will be

676
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:21,200
a focal point for their conversations.

677
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:24,320
Also, I want to invite

678
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:27,200
the very popular musician Mr. Yo-Yo Ma

679
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:29,040
and the Contemporary Ensemble

680
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:30,920
to perform live for us.

681
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:34,240
Their style is very suitable.

682
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:35,840
These two celebrities you mentioned

683
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,640
have very high appearance fees.

684
00:36:37,640 --> 00:36:39,400
They all charge by the hour.

685
00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:42,130
I've already thought about all these issues.

686
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:43,680
The selection of activities

687
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:45,600
and the dance Miss Tong Tong will perform

688
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:47,120
have all been designed by me.

689
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:50,120
And I already did a practical run-through yesterday.

690
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:53,240
Apart from the game session later,

691
00:36:53,240 --> 00:36:55,880
Miss Tong Tong's time on stage

692
00:36:56,120 --> 00:36:58,280
will only be 15 to 20 minutes.

693
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,400
So I think we should negotiate with her for

694
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:02,080
a 20-minute performance time.

695
00:37:02,080 --> 00:37:04,680
This way, we'll get excellent value for money.

696
00:37:05,160 --> 00:37:08,240
Director Shi, do you think my plan is feasible?

697
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:11,200
Beibei, can you estimate the cost?

698
00:37:12,640 --> 00:37:14,200
I've made a rough estimate.

699
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:17,800
Venue rental, staff, props, lighting, and sound

700
00:37:18,080 --> 00:37:20,210
will cost at least 500,000 to 800,000.

701
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:22,320
This doesn't include appearance fees.

702
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:24,200
Based on industry rates,

703
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:26,290
the budget for the entire event

704
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:28,240
would be at least 2 to 3 million.

705
00:37:28,920 --> 00:37:30,980
I think this plan is too extravagant.

706
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:33,480
We'd have to advance too much money upfront.

707
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:39,160
I think results are what matter most.

708
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:41,480
Although we're spending more this time,

709
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:43,000
this approach will help us

710
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,480
achieve our goal of selling products quickly.

711
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,440
Besides, I've already discussed this with Manager Li.

712
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:49,400
He approves of our plan.

713
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:54,000
Wan Xinxin, you're not acting like yourself today.

714
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,440
You've even learned to consider others' perspectives.

715
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,400
Really?

716
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:01,060
Did you create this proposal on your own?

717
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:03,000
Well, I had a friend

718
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:04,730
who helped me think it through.

719
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:07,000
What kind of person is he?

720
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:09,480
He's our housekeeper.

721
00:38:10,520 --> 00:38:13,560
No, well, this person...

722
00:38:14,680 --> 00:38:17,520
He's quite strange usually.

723
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:20,520
But he's very attentive when it comes to children.

724
00:38:20,520 --> 00:38:21,880
Must be a man, right?

725
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,120
Yes, he's a middle-aged man.

726
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:25,210
A strange uncle.

727
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:28,760
So do you like this man

728
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:30,760
and the proposal he shared with you?

729
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:33,530
Do you think it meets the client's requirements?

730
00:38:33,840 --> 00:38:36,360
I'm not sure if the client will like it.

731
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:39,080
But when I was working on this proposal,

732
00:38:39,080 --> 00:38:41,200
I was completely immersed in it.

733
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:41,920
I felt like

734
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:43,880
I was creating a fairy tale world.

735
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:48,280
Like the fairy tale I've always wanted to visit since childhood.

736
00:38:50,160 --> 00:38:51,640
Alright, Wan Xinxin,

737
00:38:52,240 --> 00:38:53,840
go ahead and create

738
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:56,170
this fairy tale for all of us to see.

739
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:00,040
You agree?

740
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:07,600
All departments, give Wan Xinxin your full support.

741
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:08,730
Meeting adjourned.

742
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:10,400
Mr. Shi

743
00:39:13,160 --> 00:39:13,840
Mr. Shi

744
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:16,320
Mr. Shi

745
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:21,120
Excellent!

746
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:27,140
I'm afraid there will be trouble if we leave everything to Wan Xinxin.

747
00:39:28,200 --> 00:39:29,080
Her mind is

748
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:31,010
already lost in a fairy tale world.

749
00:39:32,040 --> 00:39:33,300
Nothing will go wrong.

750
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:35,880
Two tigers, two tigers.

751
00:39:35,920 --> 00:39:37,840
How strange, indeed.

752
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,160
Do you speak English?

753
00:39:39,160 --> 00:39:41,200
I don't speak English.

754
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:50,400
How strange.

755
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:53,040
How did it go?

756
00:39:53,240 --> 00:39:54,480
I'm so angry!

757
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:56,840
I mean, a Chinese amusement park

758
00:39:56,840 --> 00:39:58,400
why hire a foreigner as manager?

759
00:39:58,400 --> 00:39:59,040
Listen to me.

760
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:01,560
I'd be fine if he were British or American.

761
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:03,040
But he's not even that.

762
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:04,240
Who knows if he's French or German.

763
00:40:04,240 --> 00:40:05,920
He talks so much and I can't understand a word.

764
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:07,600
I have a CET-4 certificate.

765
00:40:07,600 --> 00:40:08,460
Did you pass it?

766
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:10,140
I was six points short.

767
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:12,640
No, but I can

768
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:14,280
handle basic communication.

769
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:16,210
I can't even communicate with him.

770
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:17,000
No.

771
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:19,920
Shouldn't this foreign manager have a Chinese translator?

772
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:22,320
There is one, but they haven't arrived yet.

773
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:23,960
How long do we have to wait?

774
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:24,880
I can't communicate with him,

775
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:26,520
so how would I know how long?

776
00:40:26,520 --> 00:40:27,360
What are you doing

777
00:40:27,360 --> 00:40:28,800
holding your baby brother?

778
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:30,360
I have a ton of things to do this afternoon.

779
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:30,880
Okay, go with mom.

780
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:31,480
I need to discuss something this afternoon

781
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:33,880
about equipment for an entertainment agency.

782
00:40:33,880 --> 00:40:35,280
Wait, where are you going?

783
00:40:35,280 --> 00:40:36,600
What are you doing?

784
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:52,180
Lifting her up.

785
00:40:53,080 --> 00:40:55,640
Two tigers, two tigers.

786
00:40:55,640 --> 00:40:58,120
Running fast, running fast.

787
00:40:58,120 --> 00:41:00,720
One has no eyes, one has no tail.

788
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:02,880
How strange!

789
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,080
You sing so well.

790
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:06,160
Um, Xinxin.

791
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:07,880
He basically agreed.

792
00:41:07,880 --> 00:41:10,200
Then you and his translator

793
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:12,130
can discuss the contract details.

794
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:13,560
Thank you.

795
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:14,840
Thanks.

796
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:15,840
Your wife is lovely and suits you well.

797
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:17,720
Your family of three looks very happy.

798
00:41:17,720 --> 00:41:19,000
What did you tell him?

799
00:41:19,720 --> 00:41:20,920
You misunderstood. She's my employer.

800
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:22,200
I don't have a wife yet.

801
00:41:22,440 --> 00:41:23,800
Oh, I see.

802
00:41:24,240 --> 00:41:24,800
Goodbye.

803
00:41:25,560 --> 00:41:26,320
Thank you.

804
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:27,440
Goodbye.

805
00:41:28,840 --> 00:41:30,320
Doesn't he speak Chinese?

806
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:31,840
What Chinese?

807
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,680
He's only been in China for a few days.

808
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:36,440
Wait, how did you talk to him?

809
00:41:37,640 --> 00:41:38,400
In German.

810
00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:40,120
Besides, for them,

811
00:41:40,360 --> 00:41:42,890
having a celebrity visit is also beneficial.

812
00:41:43,720 --> 00:41:46,920
German? You old fox, you speak German?

813
00:41:47,240 --> 00:41:48,560
I stayed there for a few days.

814
00:41:48,560 --> 00:41:49,960
Did you rescue dogs in Germany too?

815
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:52,760
What are you talking about? I just stayed there for a few days.

816
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,640
You sly dog, not bad!

817
00:41:55,240 --> 00:41:56,880
You've been a huge help this time.

818
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:58,400
I must thank you properly.

819
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:00,280
You'll need to accompany me these days.

820
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:02,140
Don't worry, I'll treat you well.

821
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:04,160
I'll give you a raise later.

822
00:42:04,160 --> 00:42:04,890
An extra 200.

823
00:42:05,080 --> 00:42:06,600
Before talking about that 200 raise,

824
00:42:06,600 --> 00:42:08,260
I paid for the tickets myself.

825
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:09,920
You bought them?

826
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:13,160
No, we're clients.

827
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:16,010
We should get that foreigner to reimburse us.

828
00:42:16,120 --> 00:42:17,200
It's a 100,000 yuan contract.

829
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:18,760
Can't you be a little more generous?

830
00:42:18,760 --> 00:42:20,160
We can't lose out either.

831
00:42:20,360 --> 00:42:21,640
We brought our little star here.

832
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:22,760
We should have some fun

833
00:42:22,760 --> 00:42:24,220
and win a doll to take back.

